### CRITICAL: Required JSON Field Names

You **MUST** use these **EXACT** field names (case-sensitive):

| Field | Type | Example | Notes |
|-------|------|---------|-------|
| `id` | string | `"1"` | Sequential string IDs |
| `title` | string | `"Rex: API Endpoints"` | Include agent prefix (AgentName:) |
| `description` | string | `"Brief summary"` | One-line summary |
| `agentHint` | string | `"rex"` | **LOWERCASE** agent name |
| `dependencies` | array | `["1"]` | Array of task ID strings |
| `details` | string | `"Full implementation..."` | Detailed instructions with code signatures |
| `testStrategy` | string | `"kubectl get..."` | Verification commands |

**FORBIDDEN field names** (DO NOT USE):
- `agent` - Use `agentHint` instead
- `acceptance_criteria` - Use `details` instead
- Capitalized agent names like `"Bolt"` - Use lowercase `"bolt"`

