## Task Sizing Guidelines (CRITICAL)

**Each task MUST be completable in ONE agent iteration (~one context window).**

Agents run with fresh context per iteration. If a task is too big, the agent runs out of context before finishing.

### Right-Sized Tasks (GOOD)

| Example | Why It Works |
|---------|--------------|
| "Add user_id column + migration" | Single database change |
| "Create NotificationCard component" | Single UI component |
| "Implement POST /api/notifications" | Single endpoint |
| "Add filter to notifications list" | Single feature increment |
| "Write tests for auth middleware" | Scoped test coverage |

### Too Big (SPLIT THESE)

| Bad Task | Split Into |
|----------|------------|
| "Build entire dashboard" | Schema → API → Components → Filters |
| "Add authentication" | Schema → Middleware → Login UI → Session handling |
| "Refactor the API" | One task per endpoint or module |
| "Implement notification system" | Create → Read → Update → Delete as separate tasks |

### Rule of Thumb

> **If you can't describe the implementation in 2-3 sentences, the task is too big.**

### Task Size Checklist

Before finalizing each task:

- [ ] Can be described in 2-3 sentences?
- [ ] Touches only 1-3 files?
- [ ] Has ONE primary change (not "and also...")
- [ ] Acceptance criteria are verifiable in one PR?
- [ ] Does NOT require multiple iteration cycles?

