## Output Structure (Session 1)

**You must generate ONLY `tasks.json`**. Session 2 will generate per-task prompts from your tasks.json.

```
.tasks/
├── tasks/
│   └── tasks.json              # <-- YOU CREATE THIS (all tasks with full details)
└── docs/
    ├── prd.txt                 # Already exists (input)
    └── architecture.md         # Already exists (input, if provided)
```

### What Happens After Session 1

After your tasks.json is complete:
1. `intake split-tasks` splits tasks.json into individual task-N.json files
2. `intake generate-prompts` (Session 2) creates per-task prompts with AI research
3. Each task gets: prompt.md, prompt.xml, acceptance.md (and optionally code-examples.md)

**IMPORTANT**: Do NOT create individual task-N/ directories or per-task files. Put ALL task content (details, testStrategy, code signatures) into tasks.json. Session 2 will handle the rest.

